task.summary: Default task
Update logic in RectangleOverlap
Update documentation for finding longest path in graph
Update typo
Solve medium calculate exponent in logn by squaring
Solve medium find root of min height tree by calculating the diameter of the tree followed by finding the center of the diameter -- very good question
Solve medium find root of min height tree by removing leaf nodes one by one until only the center node remains
Solve medium divide array in sets of K consecutive numbers using treemap -- was able to almost solve it on my own
Update documentation in DeleteNodeInLinkedListWithoutHeadPointer

Solved medium shortest path to reach a node in a matrix using BFS and A* algorithm -- A* requires an heuristic function to find approximate cost to reach target along with a cost matrix which decides whether to continue this path
Solve easy find whether a string is subsequence of another string using two pointer approach
Solve medium is sudoku valid -- tricky part was to find the subgrid index using % and /, math is hard
Solve medium shuffle an array using fisher yates algorithm in the first attempt
Solve easy min cost to reach top of the stairs using DP
Solve medium number of nodes in the subtree with same label using DFS -- in case where you need to build a tree from the edges treat it similar to creation of an undirected graph
Solve medium delete node in a BST -- tricky question, need to carefully update the pointers
Update CombinationSum3 by simplifying logic
Solve easy remove elements from linked list which matches a specific key by appending the filtered keys to a dummy node
Solve medium product of array elements except self with and without extra space
Solve medium odd and even linked list by managing two dummy head/tail nodes
Solve medium GameOfLife -- good follow up questions on handling sparse matrices -- store only the information required or process row by row

Update GameOfLife to not use extra space -- state transitions can be stored in individual bits e.g. rightmost bit can store the current state, next state can be stored in the adjacent left of the rightmost bit
Update GenerateBrackets by simplifying logic
Solve medium zig-zag level order traversal using dfs
Add premium smallest common region, cool way of finding lca of two nodes by storing (node, parent) in hashmap and walking the parents for both region
Solve easy contains duplicate element by fixed sliding window implementation

Solve medium find whether numbers that lies within a range exists or not using treeSet -- got TLE while using HashSet
Use TreeSet for lower_bound / upper_bound questions
Solve medium find two single numbers in an array of duplicates by dividing the array into groups with a bit set or unset
Update documentation in RootToLeafPathSum to add condition to check whether node is leaf or not
Solve medium list all nodes at a distance K from a given node -- tricky question, need to carefully handle which subtree target lies in
Solve medium find all paths from source to target node in a DAG using DFS + Backtracking in first attempt
Solve medium find right side view of binary tree using DFS and keeping the rightmost value found in a level
Solve medium populate next right pointer in a binary tree in constant space by level order traversal -- iterate all nodes present at one level and keep updating next pointer of nodes of next level
Simplify RightSideViewOfBinaryTree by traversing right side first to prevent overriding in the result array
Move TreeNode and ListNode from default package -- apparently you can't import classes from default package
Add solution of Boundary traversal of binary tree in single traversal of tree using modified preorder traversal
Solve easy Next greater element 1 by using stack
Solve medium find Next Greater Element in a circular array in first attempt by looping the input array twice
Solve medium find number of subarrays with odd sum using maths -- very tricky and hard problem

Solve medium find number of way to split a string into two parts having equal number of distinct characters
TIP: When dealing with questions related to split, try to solve the problem left to right and right to left separately.
Solve hard find minimum no of operations to reach target array -- Don't give up early instead try to build solutions from input of size = 1, size = 2, size = 3
Solve two medium problems related to next permutation -- trick is to find which indices to swap and sort from
Solve easy digital root of a number using fixed math formula

Solve medium Bulb Switcher 4 in first attempt -- question related to reach a target state from input state
Similar to MinimumNumberOfOperationstoReachTargetArray

Solve medium find number of leaf pairs lying within a target distance using post order traversal and keeping track of {distance to leaf node, no of leaf nodes} from left/right subarray
Similar to NumberOfNodesInTheSubTreeWithSameLabel

Solve medium find minimum in rotated sorted array with and without duplicates using modified binary search. In case of duplicates, travel in both directions to find the smallest index value and resume search

Solve medium find no of subarrays with k odd numbers by transforming it to subarray sum equals k. Sliding window solution is also possible but I found it difficult to visualize.
TIP: Problems with at most K constraint can probably be solved using sliding window as well.
Simplify code in FindMinimumInRotatedSortedArray2

Solve GFG find no of ways to pair people using DP
Was asked this during my amazon onsite, absolutely failed at answering why (n-1) is required ! I memoized the solution that time without understanding the concept, this time I reached the solution on my own.
Solve medium create binary tree from inorder and postorder traversal by fixing the root first and then recursively fixing the root of left/right subarray
